### 8. Common Tool Categories

Focus on external API integration tools:

#### REST API Tools
- Follow external API pattern with HTTP methods
- Include proper error handling for network failures and HTTP errors
- Support various content types (JSON, XML, form data)
- Implement proper timeout handling

#### Authentication Patterns
- Basic Auth (username/password) as shown in template
- API Key authentication (custom headers)
- Bearer token authentication
- OAuth integration for complex auth flows

#### API Response Handling
- Parse JSON responses for structured data
- Handle different HTTP status codes appropriately
- Format response data for display
- Error message extraction from API responses

### 9. Architecture Integration

#### MCP Capabilities
Your tools automatically integrate with:
- **Streamable HTTP transport**: RESTful API calls over HTTP
- **Shared business logic**: External API integration patterns in `/mcp` package
- **Multiple clients**: Claude Desktop, Cursor IDE, and any HTTP-capable MCP clients

#### Server Configuration
The streamable HTTP server implementation:
1. Creates MCP server with tool capabilities
2. Adds API integration tools with external connectivity
3. Wraps with HTTP transport server
4. Starts listening on port 8081 for HTTP requests
5. Provides stateless API calling capabilities

## Quick Checklist for New API Tools

- [ ] Tool function name ends with "Tool"
- [ ] Clear description provided for API functionality
- [ ] All parameters have descriptions (endpoint, method, auth, etc.)
- [ ] Required vs optional parameters properly marked
- [ ] Input validation implemented for URLs and HTTP methods
- [ ] HTTP client timeout configured (30 seconds recommended)
- [ ] Basic auth header implementation included
- [ ] Appropriate error messages for network failures
- [ ] HTTP status code handling implemented
- [ ] Response formatting follows established patterns
- [ ] Tool registered in streamable HTTP server
- [ ] Function documented with API usage examples
- [ ] Tested with HTTP server implementation

## Example Integration

After creating a new API tool, it will automatically be available through:
- **Streamable HTTP**: `http://localhost:8081/mcp` (after starting server)
- **Claude Desktop**: Via configured MCP HTTP connection
- **Cursor IDE**: Via configured MCP HTTP connection
- **Any HTTP client**: Direct POST requests to `/mcp` endpoint

